  <!-- Phase 3: Go2 + Z1 arm as a welded counterweight (payload).
       This is go2.xml with the Unitree Z1 arm bolted onto base_link as DEAD WEIGHT:
         * no <joint>, no <actuator> on the arm  -> qpos stays 19, nu stays 12, env unchanged
         * arm geoms are visual-only (contype=0 conaffinity=0) -> no ground/self collision
         * each arm link keeps its real <inertial> (mass+inertia) -> correct CoM/inertia (~5.2 kg)
       The Z1 link tree (relative pos/inertials) is copied verbatim from
       TRAINING-Aliengo/aliengo_scene.xml (Felix's welded Z1), only re-rooted onto the
       Go2 base and stripped of collision geoms. Mount point is the base top center
       (pos 0 0 0.05): in the zero pose the arm hairpins backward so its CoM lands
       ~6 cm behind / 12 cm above the mount -> whole-robot CoM ~1.6 cm behind base
       center (the doc's "slightly back"), with the heavy upper arm kept horizontal
       for the lowest practical CoM. See z1_assets/RESOURCES.md and CONTINUATION §二. -->
